					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">exdeath wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">For starters, I had to enable the right mirroring mode on the MMC3, it appears to override any PPU settings.  Emulators have this wrong it seems as I never encountered it before.</div><br />Depends on the initialization value that the mapper uses for the mirroring. PowerPak is no better than emulators in this regard, it'll use whatever init values the mapper author decided to use. I guess my save state mappers happened to use the correct initial mirroring for your ROM.<br /><br />And now thinking about it, I think I deliberately changed the mirroring initialization value to horizontal mirroring to make the mappers compatible with Karnov, which has been assigned iNES MMC3 even though it doesn't use MMC3. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />The only thing that emulators arguably get wrong, from NES developers point of view, is that they don't spit out warnings when the entire mapper state hasn't been initialized.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 85%; line-height: normal">Download STREEMERZ for NES from <a href="http://www.fauxgame.com" class="postlink">www.fauxgame.com</a>!</span></div>
